{% extends "./internal/base.njk" %}

{% block style %}
ul {
  list-style-type: none;
}
{% endblock %}

{% block main %}

<h1>Themes</h1>
<p>
Rough Elements support both light and dask themes and will following the system
theme automatically.  An HTML must link to the Rough Elements default stylesheet
before importing any elements as follows:
</p>

<pre><code>&lt;!doctype html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;link href="https://esm.sh/jsr/@rough/rough-elements/public/themes/default.css" rel="stylesheet"&gt;
    ...
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    ...
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>
A theme consists of a small number of CSS properties that must be set.  The
simplest way to create a new theme is to copy the <code>default.css</code> file and change
the colours as needed.  Then load this file instead of <code>default.css</code>.
</p>
<p>
IMPORTANT: DON'T REMOVE OR RENAME ANY OF THE CLASSES, MEDIA QUERIES, CSS
SELECTORS OR CSS PROPERTIES.  SIMPLY SET THE VALUE OF THE FOLLOWING CSS
PROPERTIES TO THE DESIRED VALUES:

<ul>
<li>--primary-color</li>
<li>--success-color</li>
<li>--neutral-color</li>
<li>--warning-color</li>
<li>--danger-color</li>
<li>--foreground-color</li>
<li>--background-color</li>
</ul>
</p>

{% endblock %}
